state-data><country>BA</country></ep-extended-state-data><ep-extended-state-data><country>ME</country></ep-extended-state-data><ep-extended-state-data><country>RS</country></ep-extended-state-data></ep-extended-states></designated-states></international-convention-data></bibliographic-data><abstract mxw-id="PA128674428" lang="EN" load-source="patent-office"><p id="pa01" num="0001">In an image pickup apparatus with two image-taking lenses, the amount of feed of a first zoom lens (21) and the amount of feed of a second zoom lens (31) corresponding to a magnification of the first zoom lens and a magnification of the second zoom lens which are close to each other are associated, and the amounts of feed of the first zoom lens and the second zoom lens corresponding to an arbitrarily designated magnification are set. Accordingly, the magnifications of the first zoom lens (21) and the second zoom lens (31) can be accurately made almost equal over the entire zoom range. Since the magnifications of the first zoom lens and the second zoom lens are made equal on the basis of the amounts of feed, effective pixels do not decrease, unlike magnification correction using an electronic zoom.</p><p id="pa02" num="0002">The invention also extends to a zoom correction information creation method, a program for causing an image pickup apparatus to carry out the zoom correction information creation method, and a recording medium storing such a program.
